Fears about the rebels swept the city in the following days, although the UN peacekeeping force MINUSCA said their advance had been stopped.
The rebel coalition on Wednesday announced a 72-hour "unilateral ceasefire" in the run-up to the vote, only to call it off on Friday saying it would resume its march on the capital.



